\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {A3}{\ignorespaces Partial irreversibility of cognitive diversity under early versus late governance. $G_0$ (red): continuous unmanaged adoption, $\text  {Var}(\tau )$ declines monotonically. $G_2$~Early (green): governance from $t = 1$. $G_2$~Late (orange, dashed): governance adopted at $t = 10$ ($\approx $2.5~years). Late governance arrests the decline but cannot restore the 6\% shortfall in $\text  {Var}(\tau )$ already depleted. \textit  {V4 verification, v5 coupled model, under model assumptions.}}}{39}{figure.caption.16}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:a4}{{A3}{39}{Partial irreversibility of cognitive diversity under early versus late governance. $G_0$ (red): continuous unmanaged adoption, $\text {Var}(\tau )$ declines monotonically. $G_2$~Early (green): governance from $t = 1$. $G_2$~Late (orange, dashed): governance adopted at $t = 10$ ($\approx $2.5~years). Late governance arrests the decline but cannot restore the 6\% shortfall in $\text {Var}(\tau )$ already depleted. \textit {V4 verification, v5 coupled model, under model assumptions.}}{figure.caption.16}{}}
