\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {A4}{\ignorespaces Eight organisational profiles under $G_0$: output relative to no-AI baseline (horizontal) versus $P_{99}\times \theta $ (vertical). London and Paris share sector and talent ($E[\pi ]=0.55$, $h\in [0.65,0.95]$); their separation ($\alpha =0.45$ vs $0.90$) produces a 22\% gap in tail risk. Paris carries the highest proportional premium (+198\%), the lowest expected loss, and the steepest scaffold benefit: the numerical expression of the top-tier twist. The frontier is a governance-exposure map, not a production frontier. \textit  {V5 coupled model, $M = 200$ replications, under model assumptions.}}}{40}{figure.caption.17}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:profiles}{{A4}{40}{Eight organisational profiles under $G_0$: output relative to no-AI baseline (horizontal) versus $P_{99}\times \theta $ (vertical). London and Paris share sector and talent ($E[\pi ]=0.55$, $h\in [0.65,0.95]$); their separation ($\alpha =0.45$ vs $0.90$) produces a 22\% gap in tail risk. Paris carries the highest proportional premium (+198\%), the lowest expected loss, and the steepest scaffold benefit: the numerical expression of the top-tier twist. The frontier is a governance-exposure map, not a production frontier. \textit {V5 coupled model, $M = 200$ replications, under model assumptions.}}{figure.caption.17}{}}
